messages.message: Heyo, just wanted to send the outcome of `docker image rm instabase/webapp:latest` which was worth a shot! But yes, looks like more things broke, but yes I will look into this later
@pauline.comising which sandbox is this? i see you have `paulinecomising`, `paulinecomising1`, ... `paulinecomising5`

I ran `cs ps` on your sandbox, and you can see that nothing is running

what happened after you ran `cs start` in your sandbox?
`cs start` should start up the daemons, which should then show up if you check their status via `cs ps`
After I ran that, the sandbox disconnected, so those logs in the screenshot happened because I ran cs start
Heh ya I can try suspending and reviving one more time :woman-bowing::skin-tone-2: otherwise yes paulinecomising5 is prepped to replace it :pray:
i saw the same issue in `paulinecomising5`, so i ran `cs start` for you and it's looking a lot better
it'll take time for all the services to build though
ah thanks serena! yes, I'll check in on the services, and webapp, after its gotten a minute to boot up
